-virgin-galactics-first-ever-space-tourist-flight-at-11am-et-143100162.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 73384fd8-f36a-4bef-af5e-5387cc879c7b</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:31:00 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691668256</ingested><modified> 2023-08-10T11:51:16+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Professional Services]]></category><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="1009" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/aba94690-376b-11ee-bdff-235d6b2f3bd2" width="1600"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1009" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/aba94690-376b-11ee-bdff-235d6b2f3bd2" width="1600"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Virgin Galactic]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A photo of the Virgin Galactic 02 crew, Jon Goodwin, Keisha Schahaff and Anastasia Mayers.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Virgin Galactic]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Android phones for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>与苹果是唯一的 iOS 生态系统不同，Android 手机市场的最大优点之一是有多种不同的设备和制造商可供选择。也就是说，当真正需要升级时，丰富的选择可能会让您选择合适的手机变得更加困难。如果您正在寻找一部新手机，但不知道从哪里开始，我们会为您精选适合各种预算的最佳 Android 手机。</p><h2>购买新的 Android 手机需要注意什么</h2><h3>表现</h3><p>当谈到挑选我们最喜欢的 Android 手机时，我们寻找的主要因素非常简单：良好的性能（计算和人工智能）、漂亮的显示屏、坚固的设计、锋利的相机、长电池寿命以及对持续软件支持的重大承诺。对于性能，我们不仅会查看基准测试和其他指标，还会根据响应能力来评估手机。无论您是在阅读、浏览社交媒体还是玩游戏，没有人想要一台感觉迟缓的设备。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3>展示</h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/54f98de0-a87e-11ed-afd1-54c1e8d571fc" alt="虽然规格与去年相比没有太大变化，但三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra 的 6.8 英寸 120Hz AMOLED 显示屏仍然是市场上最好的智能手机屏幕之一。" data-uuid="f90b4b62-0619-3c10-8a7b-abccc2d7e842"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">萨姆·卢瑟福/Engadget</div></figure><p>在显示器方面，我们通常更喜欢能够产生丰富、饱和的色彩且亮度至少为 600 尼特的 OLED 面板，尽管我们的许多顶级中端和高端手机的亮度都可以达到 1,000 尼特或更高。最近，我们最喜欢的大多数设备还支持 90Hz 或 120Hz 快速刷新率的屏幕，这增加了额外的平滑度和流动性。</p><h3>设计</h3><p>现在我们承认，在决定哪些手机看起来最好时存在一些主观性，但还有其他设计方面，例如防尘防水或屏幕耐用性，可以对长期生存产生很大影响。考虑对无线充电、电源共享（又称反向无线充电）和 UWB 连接的支持等因素也很重要，这些因素可能会影响手机与其他设备的交互方式。</p><h3>相机</h3><p>显然，对于照片，我们希望在明亮和弱光条件下拍摄清晰、色彩丰富的照片。我们希望视频剪辑具有高动态范围、丰富的音频和流畅的图像稳定性。用于超广角和长焦镜头的额外相机是一个优点。考虑专用夜间模式、支持各种视频录制分辨率以及延时摄影、慢动作等其他照片模式等功能也很重要。</p><h3>电池和软件</h3><p>最后，在电池续航时间方面，我们希望设备能够拥有全天的续航时间，并且在我们的本地视频运行测试中也能取得出色的成绩（一次充电至少 16 小时，但显然越多越好）。在过去的几年里，无线充电功能几乎无处不在，我们的大多数首选产品都具有这种额外的功能。最后，随着人们使用手机的时间比以往任何时候都长，我们希望看到公司承诺至少三年的软件支持、升级和定期安全更新。</p><h2>最好的安卓手机</h2><h2></h2><h2>最佳 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="6c0fc07b5bfe47688db2b2d8968dd3ac" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtUHJvLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtVGVsZXBob3RvL2RwL0IwQkNRV1lSMlo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tbnotMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjhkZTg5YTJkLWIzNDQtNGQyMi1hZTg5LWIzMTRiNzVmY2IxZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZuzv_OntlWKtc3kU_R6DzOAL7wpXaS2FC4opPdWgj1c&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Pro-Smartphone-Telephoto%2Fdp%2FB0BCQWYR2Z">Pixel 7 Pro</a>和标准<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtNy01Ry1BbmRyb2lkLVBob25lL2RwL0IwQkNRWFk1Mlo_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAASpA5F4f1KXYW4oQgh_yMRWREBd33uFTYbfquLiIWWVt&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-7-5G-Android-Phone%2Fdp%2FB0BCQXY52Z%3Fth%3D1">Pixel 7</a>可能不是市场上绝对最快的手机，但它们在纯粹性能方面的不足可以通过周到的软件来弥补。得益于谷歌的 Tensor G2 芯片，Pixel 7 系列具有强大的人工智能和机器学习功能，支持设备上语言识别和实时翻译等功能。您还可以获得华丽的 OLED 显示屏以及当今<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html">智能手机中最佳的整体相机质量</a>。标准 Pixel 7 的起价仅为 600 美元，谷歌最新旗舰产品的价值也令人难以置信。两者之间的主要区别在于 Pixel 7 Pro 拥有更大的 6.7 英寸屏幕，并配备第三个后置摄像头，支持 ​​5 倍光学变焦。但无论您喜欢更小还是更大的设备，Pixel 7 或 Pixel 7 Pro 都不会出错。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7-and-pixel-7-pro-review-still-the-best-bargain-in-flagship-phones-170031940.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7 Pro 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳中端Android手机：OnePlus 11 </h2><p><core-commerce id="1013518286f041b7be4c6a83405b2a98" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>对于那些想要一部大屏幕、出色的摄像头和卓越性能的手机，但价格又低于传统旗舰机的人来说， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9PbmVQbHVzLVVubG9ja2VkLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtSGFzc2VsYmxhZC1Qcm9jZXNzb3IvZHAvQjBCTldRQzlGSi8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1uei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRlODlhMmQtYjM0NC00ZDIyLWFlODktYjMxNGI3NWZjYjFkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAX-H-HDCbozJUO5Ri9Pm3mvkdJEw_ZVvcGSOfpg2-wVG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOnePlus-Unlocked-Smartphone-Hasselblad-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0BNWQC9FJ%2F%3Fth%3D1">OnePlus 11</a>在廉价手机和更高端设备之间取得了良好的平衡。在很多方面，OnePlus 11 就像更实惠的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-review-a-solid-phone-thats-probably-not-worth-the-upgrade-173026346.html">Galaxy S23+</a> 。你不仅拥有类似的 6.7 英寸 120Hz 显示屏，还配备快速的 Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 芯片和 5,000 mAh 的大电池。与此同时，得益于 OnePlus 强劲的 100 瓦有线充电功能，它的充电速度比任何谷歌或三星手机都快。在相机方面，该公司与哈苏的持续合作显着提高了图像质量。</p><p> OP11的主要缺点是其IP64防尘防水等级低于竞争对手的设备，而且相机的2倍光学变焦镜头感觉有点短。但随着 OnePlus 增加了更广泛的运营商兼容性，并承诺四年的操作系统升级和五年的安全补丁，OP11 是一个装备精良的选择，成本明显低于竞争对手。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oneplus-11-review-price-release-date-cameras-150015371.html"><strong>阅读我们对 OnePlus11 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳预算 Android 手机：Google Pixel 7a </h2><p><core-commerce id="8af72094077040eea8d5a86a5802492c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>售价 500 美元的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0b3JlLmdvb2dsZS5jb20vP3BsaT0xJmhsPWVuLVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZGU4OWEyZC1iMzQ0LTRkMjItYWU4OS1iMzE0Yjc1ZmNiMWQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWBJdvYYzyh8qXtdVOgZLQuwiN_d6MKNMXdgavl3iu6b&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.google.com%2F%3Fpli%3D1%26hl%3Den-US">Pixel 7a</a>满足了我们对一款出色、价格实惠的 Android 手机的所有需求。新功能包括更快的 Tensor G2 芯片、更流畅的 90Hz 显示屏，以及首次在 Google A 系列手机上支持无线充电。它采用了 IP67 防水等级的全新设计，外观和触感与标准 Pixel 7 相似，但价格便宜 100 美元。得益于五年的安全更新和至少三年的软件更新，您还可以获得大力支持。 Pixel 7a 唯一的缺点相当小，包括缺乏专用变焦镜头以及不支持 mmWave 5G（除非您从 Verizon 购买稍微贵一点的 550 美元型号）。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-7a-review-its-got-everything-you-need-and-more-for-just-499-184517525.html"><strong>阅读我们对 Google Pixel 7a 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳优质 Android 手机：三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra </h2><p><core-commerce id="a6ef601583384a64973e928e7c0f3c94" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVe1eNCu8XYyFXTbnswQHxk2ZNnTC1JBBPVTrU2LLOhQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Factory-Unlocked-Android-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB0BLP2PY6N%2F%3Fth%3D1">Galaxy S23 Ultra</a>的起价为 1,200 美元，非常昂贵，但它具有出色的性能，几乎拥有您在智能手机中想要或需要的一切。它拥有巨大的<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html">6.8 英寸 OLED 显示屏</a>，具有 120Hz 自适应刷新率，总共五个摄像头（主摄像头、超广角摄像头、3 倍变焦、10 倍变焦和自拍摄像头）以及内置 S Pen，用于绘图和记事——服用。它还配备了 5,000 mAh 的大电池，可提供我们在任何手机上见过的最长的运行时间。随着三星对软件支持的重新承诺，您可以期待至少四次主要操作系统升级和五年定期安全补丁。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-ultra-review-specs-price-photo-and-video-take-center-stage-140034341.html"><strong>阅读我们对三星 Galaxy S23 Ultra 的完整评论</strong></a></p><h2>最佳可折叠安卓手机：三星 Galaxy Z Fold 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="7912129d0816483492efd7b56884f0ed" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Despite increased competition from the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-fold-review-the-challenger-that-samsung-needs-specs-price-170003458.html">Pixel Fold</a> , for people who want to maximize their mobile productivity, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUd8fwjqgrBUA-1vwQGHgGKNBdbfqKCIkF-kqPPuxlbD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Storage-Unlocked-Smartphone-Streaming%2Fdp%2FB0C63QGGBK" class="rapid-with-clickid">the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5</a> is still the best big foldable on the market. On the latest model, not only has Samsung added two new gestures for launching into side-by-side multitasking or switching from a full screen to a windowed app, it has also increased the number of recent apps you can see on the taskbar from two to four. The Z Fold 5&#39;s Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 chip also delivers faster performance than on the Pixel Fold, and even though it has a smaller power cell (4,400 mAh vs 4,800 mAh), it has better battery life, too. But the biggest change for this generation is Samsung&#39;s new Flex Hinge, which allows the phone to close completely flat and makes it thinner to boot. Unfortunately, its cameras are largely unchanged from last year, and with prices starting at $1,800, the Z Fold 5 isn&#39;t even remotely close to being affordable.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/galaxy-z-fold-5-review-five-years-in-samsung-is-treading-water-140002461.html"><strong>Read our full review of the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5</strong></a></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-android-phone-130030805.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8de89a2d-b344-4d22-ae89-b314b75fcb1d</guid><dc:creator> Sam Rutherford</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 10 Aug 2023 14:10:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691676605</ingested><modified> 2023-08-10T14:10:24+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/78c254a0-bd23-11ed-bb1f-7eca272d4986" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/cadc65a0-bd23-11ed-baff-10789780782f" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Here's a photo of our favorite Android phones on the market right now featuring the Google Pixel 7, Pixel 7 Pro, Pixel 6a, Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra, Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 and the OnePlus 11.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The best Android phones you can buy right now]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nine thoughts about Star Trek: Strange New Worlds’ blockbuster finale]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>下面的文章更广泛地讨论了《霸权》和《星际迷航》的剧透。</em></p><p> <strong>1.</strong>该死的地狱。我曾多次说过， <em>《奇异新世界》</em>这一季散发出一种特殊的自信。演员和工作人员作为一个无缝的整体工作，他们知道销售的信念与所销售产品的质量同样重要。团队同样提高了底线和上限，即使是最糟糕的一集也因为它所说的内容而变得糟糕，而不是因为它是如何说的。 《霸权》是最后一集，在第三季的早期委托的帮助下，一部分是胜利的一圈，另一部分是为接下来的内容做好准备。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> <strong>2.</strong>派拉蒙的高层并没有提前表示这一集将以悬念结尾。事实上，亨利·阿隆索·迈尔斯的剧本是一个出色的佯攻，暗示这一集将在最后一刻拉上地毯之前以一个令人满意的、虽然轻快的结局结束。当你第一次值班时，幸存者被传送走时，你可能没有注意到不同的传送器能量，这是情有可原的。迈尔斯的剧本和玛雅·沃维洛的导演充满了一种低层次的恐惧感，既适合<em>异</em>形式恐怖的需要，又适合结局的高风险。</p><p> <strong>3.</strong> <em>《奇异新世界》</em>在设置和支付线程方面比你想象的要聪明。在“食莲者之中”中，奥尔特加斯在被一支客队淘汰后感到被边缘化，这迫使她接受了船上飞行员的角色。在这里，她终于实现了执行任务的愿望，但当她意识到自己或多或少超出了自己的能力范围时，她最初的热情就被浇灭了。她与姆本加博士的场景强调了这一点，她承认她要把动作英雄的角色留给队长。事实上，她是最后被<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/strange-new-worlds-109-review-130012075.html">戈恩</a>人带走的船员之一，这一事实为她最终实现自己的愿望增添了更黑暗的重量。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/75074190-35fa-11ee-bfab-4d1c6f7da70d" style="height:5304px;width:7952px;" alt="西莉亚·罗斯·古丁 (Celia Rose Gooding) 在《星际迷航：奇异新世界》中饰演 Uhura，派拉蒙+ 2023 年播出。照片来源：Michael Gibson/Paramount+" data-uuid="35463a87-9770-35b1-a58d-dae6c4c22215"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">迈克尔·吉布森/派拉蒙+</div></figure><p> <strong>4.</strong>蒙哥马利·斯科特（Montgomery Scott）在上一季大结局中的纯配音客串，是对《星际迷航》基本流利的粉丝们的一次巧妙的致敬。我想这一次由马丁·奎因扮演年轻工程师，实在太诱人了，不想继续跟进。很高兴看到一个真正的佩斯利出生的苏格兰人扮演这个角色，而且有趣的是，他是继西蒙·佩吉之后第二位在各种英国喜剧节目中扮演角色的演员。如果 Quinn 还在，我会迫不及待地让 Trek 完成者观看<em>Limmy&#39;s Show</em>和<em>Derry Girls</em>观看他的早期作品，就像我在<em>《Cheers》</em>和<em>《Night Court》中观看 Brent Spiner 时一样。</em></p><p> <strong>5.</strong>我不想喋喋不休地<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-finds-the-limit-of-what-a-prequel-can-say-130027427.html">谈论前传所施加的限制</a>，因为我们现在都知道分数了。它可能会打破《星际迷航》既定叙事的边缘，但<em>《奇异新世界》</em>永远无法逃脱其最终目的地。 Young Kirk、Young Spock、Young Uhura、Young Chapel、Young Scotty 和 Young Dr. M&#39;Benga 都将在这里，活着，变成他们 1966 年的同行。你不能让这些角色中的任何一个处于危险之中，或者让你的剧集围绕提出这个问题，因为我们已经知道谁是安全的。</p><p>这就是为什么斯波克戏剧性地营救教堂的情感节奏完美地发挥了作用，但询问她的生存问题却没有。这部剧很聪明，在我们看到查普尔努力维持生计之前，只把这个问题留到了第一幕。 （请注意，在“ <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-picks-up-where-it-left-off-130025200.html">破碎的圆圈</a>”中紧急跳跃后，她还可以穿着合适的宇航服进行EVA。）但我只能以“粉丝”的身份发言，所以也许这对那些制作了<em>《奇怪的新世界》的</em>主流观众来说效果更好流媒体电视上最大的节目之一。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9b635ae0-35fa-11ee-8f7b-5e0f3c9305e9" style="height:3448px;width:5168px;" alt="《星际迷航：奇异新世界》中 L-R 伊森·派克 (Ethan Peck) 饰演斯波克 (Spock)，安森·蒙特 (Anson Mount) 饰演派克船长 (Capt. Pike)，派拉蒙+ (Paramount+) 2023 年播出。照片来源：Michael Gibson/Paramount+" data-uuid="86d30932-73fc-37a0-b222-4caeb83bca5c"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">迈克尔·吉布森/派拉蒙+</div></figure><p> <strong>6.</strong>早在 60 年代，Pike 和 Kirk 就是同一个角色，只不过序列号被锉掉了，两者都源自 60 年代中期粗犷的阳刚之气的同一个模板。双拳思考的行动者在马背上舒适地引用诗歌或讨论海军历史。这种缺乏区别在当时甚至现在都不是真正的问题，直到<em>《奇异新世界》</em>有意识地决定让柯克潜伏在派克叙事的边缘。</p><p>这意味着制作团队需要在安森·蒙特的庄重和轻松的魅力的帮助下，将派克改造为不同于他的继任者。第一季的结局清楚地表明，派克不愿先开枪，然后再提出问题，这是他的悲剧性缺陷。柯克没有这一点，这使他成为一个更好的领导者，带领企业号执行下一组任务。但安森·蒙特的陪产假和拍摄日程的缩短意味着没有时间详细研究《 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-110-a-quality-of-mercy-review-130037849.html">仁慈的品质</a>》的后果。</p><p>毕竟，他现在知道，他一手寻求和平解决方案的愿望引发了一场消灭联邦的战争。他也知道他必须忠于自己的原则，否则他可能会污染时间线，并且无法在正确的地方拯救未来Spock的生命。事实上，他无法在悬念中做出决定，这一事实与派克所经历的旅程完全一致，但很明显，如果芒特可以的话，通往这一刻的步骤将会被更多地探索。</p><p>那么，《霸权》是该剧第一次真正有机会了解派克如何试图成长为柯克的模式，尽管他觉得这很不合适。在与阿普里尔上将的第一次谈话中，他主张先开枪的政策，但不久之后他就开始考虑寻求和平解决方案。正是这两种相互竞争的冲动让派克在结局中陷入瘫痪，因为他知道无论他做什么都会危及生命。但是，你必须再次赞扬制作团队相信观众会跟上上一季发生的事情。</p><p> <strong>7.</strong> <em>《奇异新世界》</em>只能在派克和柯克之间划清界限，这并不好。你不能让派克看起来太老派或无用，而不会让他与观众疏远，特别是考虑到他即将做出的最终牺牲。但如果反其道而行之，派克就会变得鸽派，而与鹰派的柯克相比，在我看来，这似乎是在传递错误的信息。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/ee5618a0-35fa-11ee-bcef-2a97b0e28315" style="height:5304px;width:7952px;" alt="《星际迷航：奇异新世界》中 L-R 伊森·派克 (Ethan Peck) 饰演斯波克 (Spock)，丽贝卡·罗梅恩 (Rebecca Romijn) 饰演乌娜 (Una)，派拉蒙+ (2023 年) 播出。照片来源：Michael Gibson/Paramount+" data-uuid="2bdac8f7-b1cb-396c-afed-de3e37c605ee"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">迈克尔·吉布森/派拉蒙+</div></figure><p> <strong>8.</strong>很难知道<em>《奇异新世界》</em>会持续多久，或者未来有什么计划。你可以很容易地争辩说，在你重建 1966 年的整体之前，它永远不需要结束，只需更换角色即可。每一代派拉蒙高管都渴望重蹈柯克和史波克的覆辙，希望仅靠他们的名字就能拍出一部连续剧。</p><p>但我很好奇这是否是人们真正想要的？我不确定我是否愿意，但我的梦想是制作一个以《迷航》现在为背景的原创系列，完全没有传统角色。我知道，与那些希望在《迷航》过去的安全环境中再次在怀旧跑步机上奔跑的人们相比，这种观点只是少数。 （如果不出意外的话，至少<em>《奇异新世界》</em>将其粉丝服务保持在最低限度，并尽可能地尝试走自己的路。）</p><p> <strong>9.</strong>在我的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-110-a-quality-of-mercy-review-130037849.html">第一季大结局评论</a>结束时，我写道：“朋友们，小声说吧，但<em>奇怪的新世界</em>实际上可能很好？”这在当时是一条公平的路线，因为这部剧<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-preview-040051197.html">花了一段时间</a>才进入高潮。然而，从那时起，每一集都或多或少地比上一集有所改进，从而产生了几乎没有任何弱点的第二季。我们现在不需要窃窃私语， <em>《奇异新世界》</em>是流媒体时代最好的真人迷航。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/nine-thoughts-about-star-trek-strange-new-worlds-blockbuster-finale-130046409.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nine-thoughts-about-star-trek-strange-new-worlds-blockbuster-finale-130046409.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 65d0ef0f-a3e4-40e5-91ee-de9d480eef89</guid><dc:creator> Daniel Cooper</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:00:46 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691509683</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T15:48:10+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Television]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="5304" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/92019490-35f9-11ee-bb7f-ee9f3425bac1" width="7952"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="5304" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/92019490-35f9-11ee-bb7f-ee9f3425bac1" width="7952"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Michael Gibson/Paramount+]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[L-R Rong Fu as Mitchell, Rebecca Romijn as Una, Ethan Peck as Spock and Anson Mount as Capt. Pike in Star Trek: Strange New Worlds streaming on Paramount+, 2023. Photo Credit: Michael Gibson/Paramount+]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Hegemony ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming laptops for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> For a few years now, gaming laptops have been some of the most intriguing PCs around. They&#39;ve gotten thinner and lighter, naturally — but they&#39;ve also become vastly more powerful and efficient, making them suitable for both work and play. They&#39;ve adopted some bold innovations, like rotating hinges and near desktop-like customizability. Gaming laptops are where PC makers can get adventurous.</p><p> If you&#39;re a professional in the market for a beefy new computer, and you like to play a few rounds of Apex Legends on occasion, it may make more sense to go for a gaming notebook instead of an Apple MacBook Pro workstation or the like. You&#39;ll still get plenty of power for video encoding and 3D rendering, plus you may end up paying less. We&#39;ll help you figure out which is the best gaming laptop for you, from budget options like the Dell G15 to premium notebooks like the Razer Blade 15 and everything in between. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/1c6ceae0-e935-11ea-9d63-fcfd47b39fd9" alt="ASUS ROG G14" data-uuid="c9c32383-a076-3311-b097-70654cf5e3c1"><figcaption> Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</figcaption></figure><h2><br> What&#39;s your budget?</h2><p> Your laptop buying journey starts and ends with the amount of money you&#39;re willing to spend.这并不奇怪。 The good news: There are plenty of options for gamers of every budget. In particular, we&#39;re seeing some great entry-level PC gaming choices under $1,000, like Dell&#39;s G15 lineup. A cheap gaming laptop in this price range will definitely feel a bit flimsier than pricier models, and they&#39;ll likely skimp on RAM, storage and overall power. But most cheaper laptops should be able to handle the majority of video games running at 1080p at 60 frames per second, which is the bare minimum you&#39;d want from any system.</p><p> Things get interesting when you start looking at the best gaming laptops in the mid-range space, with prices at $1,000 and higher. At that point, you&#39;ll start finding PCs like the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-amd-ryzen-radeon-173016459.html">ASUS Zephyrus ROG G14</a> , one of our favorite gaming notebooks. In general, you can look forward to far better build quality than budget laptops (metal cases!), improved graphics power and enough RAM and storage space to handle the most demanding games. These are the gaming machines we&#39;d recommend for most people, as they&#39;ll keep you gaming and working for years before you need to worry about an upgrade.</p><p> If you&#39;re willing to spend around $1,800 or more, you can start considering more premium options like Razer&#39;s Blade. Expect impeccably polished cases, the fastest hardware on the market, and ridiculously thin designs. The sky&#39;s the limit here: Alienware&#39;s uber customizable Area 51m is an enormous beast that can cost up to $4,700. Few people need a machine that high-end, but if you&#39;re a gamer with extra cash to burn, it may be worth taking a close look at some of these pricier systems. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/a3e1f580-e933-11ea-bf65-73681726b0ba" alt="Origin Evo16" data-uuid="4a48e7b5-427c-3293-87a2-1f30ac1128e6"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2><br> What kind of CPU and GPU do you want?</h2><p> The answer to this question used to be relatively simple: Just get an Intel chip with an NVIDIA GPU. But over the last few years AMD has stepped up its game with its Ryzen notebook processors, which are better suited for juggling multiple tasks at once (like streaming to Twitch while blasting fools in Fortnite). Intel responded with its impressive 12th and 13th-gen chips, but it&#39;s nice to have decent Ryzen AMD alternatives available, especially since they&#39;re often cheaper than comparable Intel models.</p><p> When it comes to video cards, though, AMD is still catching up. Its Radeon RX 6000M GPU has been a fantastic performer in notebooks like <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-rog-strix-g15-advantage-review-amd-radeon-rx-6000m-120031416.html">ASUS&#39;s ROG Strix G15</a> , but it lags behind NVIDIA when it comes to newer features like ray tracing. (We&#39;re still waiting to test AMD&#39;s new Radeon 7000 series mobile graphics.) At the very least, a Radeon-powered notebook can approach the general gaming performance of the NVIDIA RTX 3070 and 3080 GPUs.</p><p> If you want to future-proof your purchase, or you&#39;re just eager to see how much better ray tracing can make your games look, you&#39;re probably better off with an NVIDIA video card. They&#39;re in far more systems, and it&#39;s clear that they have better optimized ray tracing technology. NVIDIA GeForce RTX GPUs also feature the company&#39;s DLSS technology, which uses AI to upscale games to higher resolutions. That&#39;ll let you play a game like <em>Destiny 2</em> in 4K with faster frame rates. That&#39;s useful if you&#39;re trying to take advantage of a high refresh rate monitor.</p><p> You&#39;ll still find plenty of laptops with NVIDIA&#39;s older RTX 30-series GPUs these days, and they&#39;ll still give you tremendous performance. But to be safe, it&#39;s probably worth opting for the newer RTX 40-series systems, since they support the newer DLSS 3 technology and offer a wealth of performance upgrades. (If you&#39;re looking out for the best deals, you can probably find some killer RTX 3070 laptops out there.) The entry-level RTX 4050 is a solid start, but we&#39;d suggest going for a 4060 or 4070 if you&#39;re aiming to maximize your framerates on faster screens. The RTX 4080 and RTX 4090 are both incredibly powerful, but they typically make systems far too expensive for most users.</p><p> It&#39;s worth noting that NVIDIA&#39;s mobile GPUs aren&#39;t directly comparable to its more powerful desktop hardware. PC makers can also tweak voltages to make gaming performance better in a thinner case. Basically, don&#39;t be surprised if you see notebooks that perform very differently, even if they&#39;re all equipped with the same GPU. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/22960650-e934-11ea-92de-9913d49e86b1" alt="雷蛇灵刃 15" data-uuid="4f9811ff-53fe-37d3-bd55-dbe2ef195155"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2><br> What kind of screen do you want?</h2><p> Screen size is a good place to start when judging gaming notebooks. In general, 15-inch laptops will be the best balance of immersion and portability, while larger 17-inch models are heftier, but naturally give you more screen real estate. There are some 13-inch gaming notebooks, like the Razer Blade Stealth, but paradoxically you&#39;ll often end up paying more for those than slightly larger 15-inch options. We&#39;re also seeing plenty of 14-inch options, like the Zephyrus G14 and Blade 14, which are generally beefier than 13-inch laptops while still being relatively portable.</p><p> But these days, there is plenty to consider beyond screen size. For one: refresh rates. Most monitors refresh their screens vertically 60 times per second, or at 60Hz. That&#39;s a standard in use since black and white NTSC TVs. But over the past few years, displays have evolved considerably. Now, 120Hz 1080p screens are the bare minimum you&#39;d want in any gaming notebook — and there are faster 144Hz, 240Hz and even 360Hz panels. All of this is in the service of one thing: making everything on your display look as smooth as possible.</p><p> For games, higher refresh rates also help eliminate screen tearing and other artifacts that could get in the way of your frag fest. And for everything else, it just leads to a better viewing experience. Even scrolling a web page on a 120Hz or faster monitor is starkly different from a 60Hz screen. Instead of seeing a jittery wall of text and pictures, everything moves seamlessly, as if you&#39;re unwinding a glossy paper magazine. Going beyond 120Hz makes gameplay look even more responsive, which to some players gives them a slight advantage. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/821d1030-e936-11ea-9d7f-aed162772f3d" alt="Gigabyte Aero 15" data-uuid="5bf22bf9-dcbe-3c68-8aee-ccf82ff50f7b"><figcaption> Steve Dent/Engadget</figcaption></figure><p> Not to make things more complicated, but you should also keep an eye out for NVIDIA&#39;s G-SYNC and AMD&#39;s FreeSync. They&#39;re both adaptive sync technologies that can match your screen&#39;s refresh rate with the framerate of your game. That also helps to reduce screen tearing and make gameplay smoother. Consider them nice bonuses on top of a high refresh rate monitor; they&#39;re not necessary, but they can still offer a slight visual improvement.</p><p><strong>也可以看看：</strong></p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-120008636.html"><strong>Best Laptops for 2023</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-affordable-windows-laptops-123000512.html"><strong>Best Cheap Windows Laptops</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-2-in-1-laptops-173038508.html"><strong>Best 2-in-1 Laptops for 2023</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html"><strong>Best Chromebooks</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-for-students-130054631.html"><strong>Best Laptops for College Students</strong></a></p></li></ul><p> One more thing: Most of these suggestions are related to LCD screens, not OLEDs. While OLED makes a phenomenal choice for TVs, it&#39;s a bit more complicated when it comes to gaming laptops. They&#39;re mostly limited to 60Hz, though some models offer 90Hz. Still, you won&#39;t see the smoothness of a 120Hz or 144Hz screen. OLEDs also typically come as 4K or 3.5K panels – you&#39;ll need a ton of GPU power to run games natively at that resolution. They look incredible, with the best black levels and contrast on the market, but we think most gamers would be better off with an LCD. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/7a4d3480-e935-11ea-9ffa-4c77ce132136" alt="ASUS ROG G14" data-uuid="4bbe8bbe-f37d-3ae2-9ca5-2fcf2d064b79"><figcaption> Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</figcaption></figure><h3><br> A few other takeaways:</h3><ul><li><p> Get at least 16GB of RAM. And if you&#39;re planning to do a ton of multitasking while streaming, 32GB is worth considering.</p></li><li><p> Storage is still a huge concern. These days, I&#39;d recommend aiming for a 1TB M.2 SSD, which should be enough space to juggle a few large titles like Destiny 2. (If you can afford the jump to a 2TB SSD though, just do it.) Some laptops also have room for standard SATA drives, which are far cheaper than M.2&#39;s and can hold more data.</p></li><li><p> Get your hands on a system before you buy it. I&#39;d recommend snagging the best gaming laptop for you from a retailer with a simple return policy, like Amazon or Best Buy. If you don&#39;t like it, you can always ship it back easily.</p></li><li><p> Don&#39;t forget about accessories! For the best performance, you&#39;ll need <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-03-16-the-best-gaming-mouse.html">a good mouse</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-12-06-how-to-buy-gaming-keyboard-2018.html">keyboard</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-16-how-to-buy-a-gaming-headset.html">headphones</a> .<br></p></li></ul><h2> Best overall: ASUS ROG Zephyrus G14</h2><p><core-commerce id="c61b76c3a3304401935acc6f47b1989c" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you can&#39;t tell by now, we really like the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwODhQREI2M1o_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYXQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQzNjJhYWI0LTgwOGUtMzM5ZC05NmNkLTcwMTg5MWQ1NzAwMCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAVdU3ljcyMunRp3l1YUqc8x7MVN4kZk4MbsSfWC8F31R&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB088PDB63Z">Zephyrus G14</a> . It&#39;s shockingly compact, at just 3.5 pounds, and features AMD&#39;s new Ryzen chips paired together with its Radeon 6000M graphics (we&#39;d recommend the Ryzen 9 model with an RX 6700M for $1,400). While its 14-inch screen is a bit smaller than our other recommendations, it looks great and features a fast 144Hz refresh rate. We also like its retro-future design (some configurations have tiny LEDs on its rear panel for extra flair). While the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-190037967.html">G14</a> has jumped in price since it debuted, it&#39;s still one of the best gaming notebooks around, especially since ASUS has finally added a built-in webcam.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-amd-ryzen-radeon-173016459.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of ASUS ROG Zephyrus G14</strong></a></p><h2> Best budget: Dell G15</h2><p><core-commerce id="d0fbcfc300994f6bae7bda8088cff01b" data-type="product-list"></p><p> We&#39;ve been fans of Dell&#39;s G5 line ever since it first appeared a few years ago. Now dubbed the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQDQavbARvn12lh8gWWj9FABnXmHlI8rlZ5QPlPndIE1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDell-G15-5520-Gaming-Laptop%2Fdp%2FB09WQBS587">G15</a> , it starts at under $1,000 and, while not the most powerful gaming laptop, it features all of the latest hardware, like Intel&#39;s 13th-generation CPUs and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 40-series cards. (You can also find <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienware-m15-dell-g15-amd-ryzen-cpu-130014937.html">AMD Ryzen chips</a> in some models.) This budget-friendly gaming laptop is a bit heavy, weighing over five pounds, but it&#39;s a solid notebook otherwise. And you can even bring it into mid-range gaming territory if you spec up to the RTX 4060.</p><h2> Best premium gaming laptop: Razer Blade 15</h2><p><core-commerce id="5a9394fa7ebe47999cf5786abfba648d" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Razer continues to do a stellar job of delivering bleeding-edge hardware in a sleek package that would make Mac users jealous. The <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9SYXplci1CbGFkZS1HYW1pbmctTGFwdG9wLVRodW5kZXJib2x0L2RwL0IwOVJCSkM4WTk_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYXQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQzNjJhYWI0LTgwOGUtMzM5ZC05NmNkLTcwMTg5MWQ1NzAwMCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeEZ03GyGAvrKUobmJH32FlbeBVQkYjxHEHfZUOlsJ_7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Blade-Gaming-Laptop-Thunderbolt%2Fdp%2FB09RBJC8Y9">Blade 15</a> has just about everything you&#39;d want for great gaming, including NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 4080, Intel&#39;s 13th-gen CPUs and speedy quad-HD screens. Our recommendation? Consider the model with a Quad HD 165Hz screen and an RTX 4060 GPU for $2,500. You can easily save some cash by going for a cheaper notebook, but they won&#39;t feel nearly as polished as the Blade.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/razer-blade-15-2022-review-a-real-treat-if-youve-got-the-cash-160032467.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Razer Blade 15</strong></a></p><h2> Another good option: Acer Predator Triton 500 SE</h2><p><core-commerce id="170ad31f49834bfaa4dc9a7f7641ad08" data-type="product-list"></p><p> While we&#39;ve seen some wilder concepts from Acer, like its 360-degree hinge-equipped Triton 900, the <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUw0BXEzBSg9fFaoSxlDlV756duKUnNYi51vCnRdO0Fc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09TBPWQ34%2F">Triton 500</a> is a more affordable bread and butter option. This year, it&#39;s bumped up to a 16-inch display, giving you more of an immersive gaming experience. It&#39;s relatively thin, weighs just over five pounds, and it can be equipped with Intel&#39;s 11th-gen CPUs and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 30-series GPUs. Acer&#39;s build quality is as sturdy as ever, and it has most of the standard features you&#39;d need in a gaming notebook.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/acer-predator-triton-500-se-review-183526914.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Acer Predator Triton 500 SE Gaming Laptop</strong></a></p><h2> Best large gaming laptop: Alienware m18</h2><p><core-commerce id="8cbd2913156c47548c3e8a8d8032af2c" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVi0W8PfHT6q8wJVAernCYX9T4nFwo1u5yWeNCWMf3Cc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fgaming-laptops%2Falienware-m18-gaming-laptop%2Fspd%2Falienware-m18-r1-laptop">Alienware&#39;s m18</a> is its biggest gaming laptop ever, and it packs in just about everything we&#39;d want including a <em>really</em> big screen. It can be equipped with Intel and AMD&#39;s fastest CPUs, as well as NVIDIA&#39;s fastest GPUs (including the 4090). Its base configuration with an RTX 4060 is also surprisingly affordable for an 18-inch laptop, starting at $2,100. We&#39;ve always liked Alienware&#39;s m-series gaming laptops, but this year they&#39;re more refined, with better cooling and a slightly sleeker design. You can also opt for CherryMX mechanical keys, which deliver a desktop-like gaming and typing experience.</p><h2> Best with a dual screen: ASUS ROG Zephyrus Duo 16</h2><p><core-commerce id="b0532de86cd540c1a1683bc7a8e94745" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p><p>You know if you actually need a dual-screen laptop: Maybe a single 17-inch screen isn&#39;t enough, or you want a mobile setup that&#39;s closer to a multi-monitor desktop. If that&#39;s the case, the <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdmL5ixpdITYH7C1PwkWNPOzJOOGww3IiHZHQWMD3zTj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09YN6PTYM%2F">Zephyrus Duo 16</a> is the best laptop for you. It&#39;s powerful, and its extra 14-inch screen can easily let you multitask while<del>赌博</del>dutifully working. It also has all of the latest hardware you&#39;d want, like AMD&#39;s new Ryzen chips and NVIDIA&#39;s RTX 4000 GPUs. Sure, it&#39;s nowhere near portable, but a true multitasker won&#39;t mind.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-rog-zephyrus-duo-16-review-when-two-screens-are-better-than-one-specs-price-120018789.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of ASUS ROG Zephyrus Duo 16 Gaming Laptop</strong></a></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4362aab4-808e-339d-96cd-701891d57000</guid><dc:creator> Devindra Hardawar</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:15:15 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691669716</ingested><modified> 2023-08-10T12:15:29+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[news]]></category><category><![CDATA[Dell]]></category><category><![CDATA[gaming]]></c